name: QLThumbnailError
desc: Error information that might return when you generate a thumbnail.

items.name: init(Code, userInfo: [String : Any])
items.desc: Creates a thumbnail error from the specified code.

items.name: var code: Code
items.desc: A code that indicates the type of error.

items.name: var errorCode: Int
items.desc: A number that represents the error code.

items.name: var localizedDescription: String
items.desc: A string containing the localized description of the error.

items.name: static var errorDomain: String
items.desc: A string containing the error domain.

items.name: static var generationFailed: QLThumbnailError.Code
items.desc: The thumbnail couldn’t be created for the given file.

items.name: static var noCachedThumbnail: QLThumbnailError.Code
items.desc: A low-quality thumbnail couldn’t be created.

items.name: static var noCloudThumbnail: QLThumbnailError.Code
items.desc: The thumbnail for a remote file couldn’t be created.

items.name: static var requestCancelled: QLThumbnailError.Code
items.desc: The request to create a thumbnail was canceled.

items.name: static var requestInvalid: QLThumbnailError.Code
items.desc: The request to create a thumbnail was invalid, for example, there’s no file at a provided URL.

items.name: static var savingToURLFailed: QLThumbnailError.Code
items.desc: The thumbnail couldn’t be saved at the given URL.

items.name: enum QLThumbnailError.Code
items.desc: Error codes that may be returned when generating a thumbnail.

items.name: static func != (QLThumbnailError, QLThumbnailError) -> Bool
items.desc: Returns a Boolean value that indicates whether two thumbnail errors aren’t equal.

items.name: static func == (QLThumbnailError, QLThumbnailError) -> Bool
items.desc: Returns a Boolean value that indicates whether two thumbnail errors are equal.

items.name: var hashValue: Int
items.desc: The hash value of the thumbnail error.

items.name: func hash(into: inout Hasher)
items.desc: Hashes the essential components of the value by feeding them into the specified hasher.
